Perfect. This class is the full OTP engine for your app: generate, send, verify, and track temporary verification status.

See the file here: OtpService.cs

High-level role

Handles Phone OTP (Twilio SMS)
Handles Email OTP (SMTP, with Brevo API fallback)
Stores OTPs in memory for 5 minutes
Marks phone/email as verified for 10 minutes after correct OTP
Core fields

_config: reads settings from app configuration (.env + appsettings)
_httpClientFactory: creates HTTP clients for Twilio and Brevo API calls
_logger: writes logs for success/failure
PendingOtps: in-memory OTP store, key -> (otp, expiry)
VerifiedPhones / VerifiedEmails: in-memory short-term verified flags
SendPhoneOtpAsync(phone)

Validates empty input
Normalizes phone format (removes spaces, dashes, brackets)
Adds + if digits only
Validates final format and length
Generates 6-digit OTP
Saves OTP in PendingOtps for 5 minutes
Calls SendSmsAsync
If SMS fails, removes OTP from memory
Returns success/failure + message
SendEmailOtpAsync(email)

Validates empty input
Normalizes to lowercase
Validates email using MailAddress parser
Generates 6-digit OTP
Saves OTP in PendingOtps for 5 minutes
Calls SendEmailAsync
If email fails, removes OTP from memory
VerifyPhoneOtp(phone, otp)

Validates inputs
Normalizes phone
Builds phone key
Calls VerifyOtpInternal(key, otp)
If valid:
marks phone verified for 10 minutes in VerifiedPhones
If invalid:
logs warning
VerifyEmailOtp(email, otp)

Same logic as phone verification
Uses email key and VerifiedEmails dictionary
IsPhoneVerified / IsEmailVerified

Checks if verification exists and not expired
Used during registration to allow only verified users
ClearPhoneVerification / ClearEmailVerification

Removes verified flags after successful registration
Prevents reuse of old verification state
Helper methods

NormalizePhone: standardizes phone input
PhoneKey / EmailKey: creates stable keys
VerifyOtpInternal:
checks if OTP exists
checks expiry
checks match
removes OTP once used
SendSmsAsync(toPhone, otp)

Checks Twilio config exists
Builds Twilio HTTP request to Messages endpoint
Sends Basic Auth header using SID:Token
On failure, tries to parse Twilio JSON error and returns readable message
SendEmailAsync(toEmail, otp)

Checks SMTP config exists
Reads SMTP host/port/credentials/from email
For Brevo relay host, tries ports 587, 2525, 465
Attempts SMTP send on each port
If all SMTP attempts fail:
if Brevo API key exists, tries SendEmailViaBrevoApiAsync over HTTPS
if no API key, returns clear message that API key is missing
Handles recipient errors, SMTP errors, and generic exceptions with detailed messages
Config checkers

IsSmtpConfigured: requires host, username, password, from email
IsTwilioConfigured: requires account sid, auth token, from phone
HasBrevoApiKey: checks if Brevo API key is present
SendEmailViaBrevoApiAsync

Uses Brevo API key
Sends POST to Brevo transactional email endpoint
Payload includes sender, recipient, subject, OTP text
Returns Email sent on success, else status-based failure message
